<br>
In the past, we had tremendous success against these dragons using very few non-guild members.  I'm not sure what happened since last May or June to change this, but things have gone downhill.  Unfortunatly, with this many loses so close together, people have a tendancy to forget the successes and dwell on the failures.  I don't feel it is my place to appologize on behalf of other people, but I would hope this helps others to understand why a few CO members have made some very emotional and angry posts on these boards of late.<br>
<br>
I think we will, as a guild, probably lay off Vox and Nagafen for awhile, but once again, I'm only speaking of what we are discussing, nothing has been decided.  We want to get back to basics (so to speak) and get our sense of success back before we go in and begin to look at what went wrong.  I'd also like to say, and will post on that thread, that I totally agree with the suggested rotation plan on Vox and Naggy and *believe* that the rest of CO will feel the same way after I bring it up to the other officers.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time,<br>
<br>
